** TODO [[http://citeseerx.ist.psu.edu/viewdoc/download%3Frep%3Drep1&type%3Dpdf&doi%3D10.1.1.205.7310][JOSEPHSON BEHAVIOR IN SMALL NORMAL ONE-DIMENSIONAL RINGS]]
The k specifying the Bloch state in fig. 2 is determined by the flux \Phi  through the ring, evaluated
modulo  the flux quantum \Phi_0, = fit/e. The specific relationship is k = -k_0 \Phi/\Phi_0. where k_0 is
the zone width.
